
cron: the job scheduler, allows → Linux/user[users] to schedule jobs (comands, shell scripts) so that the run periodically or at given dates.

Often, cron is used for system maintenance/administration purposes.

sa:

 → Linux/cron/crontab

 → Linux/fhs/etc/crontab

 → Linux/fhs/etc/cron_d,
 → Linux/fhs/etc/cron_daily,
 → Linux/fhs/etc/cron_hourly,
 → Linux/fhs/etc/cron_monthly,
 → Linux/fhs/etc/cron_weekly
